subSubSection.paragraph:
Biology. In China , this species reproduces sexually, has one generation per year and overwinters as mated adult females. The females mainly feed on the stem, branches and upper leaf surfaces, whereas the males feed on the petioles and lower leaf surfaces. Once the crawler has settled, the remaining instars develop in the same spot ( Zeng & He 1939 ;
Tao et al . 2003
;
Xia et al . 2005
;
Huang et al . 2007
).
